  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support IDP families in Herat with Shelter, WASH and NFI</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is to support 200 HHs through providing Emergency shelters, plastic sheets, cash for NFIs, WASH including drinking water and hygiene protection in Shaidaee Area of Herat City. 
o	Awareness raising through REFLECT method for women and men. This will include personal hygiene, protection of old, children and women, reporting GBV and proper utilization of scare resources and so on.
o	Conducting 20 sessions on hygiene to a total of 1400 people 
o	Distributing hygiene kits to 200 HHs
o	Providing emergency shelters to the most vulnerable and needy HHs identified through needs assessment 
o	Providing plastic sheets to 200 HHs
o	Providing cash for NFIs to most vulnerable and needy HHs (preference will be given to women headed HHs) to enable IDPs to meet their needs other than directly covering by this project 
o	Procuring and distributing jerry cans (two jerry cans to each HH)
o	Providing drinking water (through water tank)</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive plastic sheets (two sheets per each HH)
&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive drinking water for 60 days
&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive jerry cans (two jerry cans per each HH)
&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive hygiene kits
&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive cash for NFIs
&#x2022;	100 HHs will receive emergency shelter (one tent and two tarps per each HH)
&#x2022;	200 HHs will receive hygiene training</narrative>
  </description>
